  "summary": "pino-zod ships postinstall agent and Discord/HuggingFace relay code — needs human review",
  "details": "Package advertises itself as a pino+zod logging integration but ships substantial unrelated infrastructure: a postinstall script (`scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs`) that runs at install time and performs network operations (GET/ping); a `discordRelayUpload.js` module containing POST upload logic and base64-encoded blobs; a `relayServer.js` with multiple ping calls; a `secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js` that issues `fetch()` calls to `https://huggingface.co`; an `hfCredentials.js` module that base64-decodes embedded data; and a `deploymentDefaults.js` containing several `Buffer.from(..., 'base64')` decodes. The combination of a postinstall hook with network activity, hardcoded relay endpoints, embedded base64 blobs decoded into credentials, and bundled secret-scanning that posts to external services is highly inconsistent with the package's stated purpose (pino logging + zod schema validation). Without a confirmed trace of the exact data flow, the disposition is review pending human inspection of the postinstall agent and the relay/credentials modules to determine whether installer environment data, credentials, or scanned secrets are exfiltrated.",
